    <text>
        <body>
            <div xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to László Macedóniai (Linz, 18 March 1530)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1"> At last he has learned that Macedóniai went to the King
                            to deal with his own and László Ország’s affairs; before he had not even
                            known where he was and was surprised that he had forgotten about his
                            friends. Now he can repair things if he will write what is happening in
                            Prague.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/FF673F47-40BC-454A-9E8C-E931B6CE74AD
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ad eundem.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Dum meas proximas ad te misissem, nuntiatum mihi est te ad
                        regem<note xml:id="note.1">Because King Ferdinand I was in Prague, see
                        below.</note> esse profectum, tum in tuis, tum in <persName>Ladislai
                        Orzagh</persName><note xml:id="note.2">László Országh of Gúth (†1544), later
                        Master Seneschal <hi rend="italic">(magister dapiferorum)</hi> between
                        1534–1542, and <hi rend="italic">ispán</hi> of Heves county between
                        1536–1544.</note> negotiis. Placuit mihi tua profectio, qui iamdudum sine
                    utilitate et tua et amicorum nescio quibus in latebris delitueris. Miror tamen
                    te adeo factum esse <del corresp="Olahus">taciturum</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                        type="corr">taciturnum</add>, ut amicos tuos <add corresp="Olahus"
                        type="insert">litteris</add> non modo non invisere, sed ne consolari plenus
                    iam tu in aula rerum novarum digneris. </p>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/83838E90-EFE6-4FC0-97DD-B2DAF147CD20
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Arbitrabar te veteris tuae naturae esse oblitum, qua saepius <del
                        corresp="Olahus">amicis videbaris negligenter</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                        type="corr">in amicos videbaris negligens</add> esse, sed nunc video te non
                    modo illius non esse immemorem, sed <quote xml:id="quote.1">eam in te radices
                        fixisse, quam nisi violenter, exstirpare minime possis</quote><note
                        type="quote" xml:id="note.quote.1">Cf. Iohannes Tröster <hi rend="italic"
                            >Dialogus de remedio amoris:</hi> „an ut accusabile malum ita etiam
                        evitabile eradicabileque sit, si et fixum sedet, vel optabile, honestum,
                        bonum amorem dicam”, see <hi rend="smallcap">Rupprich</hi> 1938,
                    182.</note>.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">Sed fac, vim quandam tibi adhibe, <quote xml:id="quote.2">invita
                        etiam Minerva</quote><note type="quote" xml:id="note.quote.2">Cic. <hi
                            rend="italic">Off.</hi> I,31,110; Hor. <hi rend="italic">Ars p.</hi>
                        385. Eras. <hi rend="italic">Adag.</hi> I,I,42: “invita Miverva”, see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Mynors</hi> 1982, 91.</note> tuis amicis cura
                    satisfacere et scribe aliquando, ne te negligentiae omnes quotquot summus
                    arguere possimus. Nunc occasionem habes scribendi, de rebus praesertim his, quae
                        <placeName>Pragae</placeName> vel tractantur, vel iam actae sunt. Ex quibus
                    omnis nostra spes pendet, et liberationis nostrae ab exilio constans fiducia.
                    Quare sis amicorum tuorum non immemor, et praebe te talem, qualem amici te
                    existimant. Vale et commenda me et fidelia mea servitia regi.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.5">Ex <placeName>Lincio</placeName> 18. Martii 1530.</p>
            </div>
